paragraphs.title: Creating the Training Function
paragraphs.text:
%python

# Split a data set, either into two (frac is a real number between 0 and 1, the fraction of the data set in the first split) or into
# a number of splits equal to the length of frac, a list of positive real numbers.
def randomsplit(df, frac):
    try:
        split1 = df.sample(frac=frac)
        split2 = df.drop(split1.index,axis="rows")
        return [split1, split2]
    except TypeError:
        splits = []
        temp = df.copy()
        for i in range(len(frac)-1):
            splits.append(temp.sample(frac=frac[i]/sum(frac[i:])))
            temp = temp.drop(splits[-1].index,axis="rows")
        splits.append(temp)
        return splits

# Arguably, we might be cross-contaminating our training and testing pools if we simply sample encounters, since some of our data
# involves patient histories. The sampleby string will allow us to sample by patient instead of by encounter, eliminating this possibility.
def get_data_sets(fulldata,labelcol="MxWillReAdmit",sampleby="",frac=[.7,.2,.1]):

    if sampleby == "":
        trainingData, testingData, verificationData = randomsplit(fulldata, frac)
    
    else:
        splits = randomsplit(fulldata[[sampleby]].drop_duplicates(), frac)
        trainingData = fulldata.merge(splits[0],on=sampleby).drop(sampleby,axis="columns")
        testingData = fulldata.merge(splits[1],on=sampleby).drop(sampleby,axis="columns")
        verificationData = fulldata.merge(splits[2],on=sampleby).drop(sampleby,axis="columns")
    
    def get_x_and_y(data,labelcol):
        x = np.array(data.drop(labelcol,axis="columns"))
        y = np.array(data[labelcol])
        return x,y

    x_training, y_training = get_x_and_y(trainingData,labelcol)
    x_testing, y_testing = get_x_and_y(testingData,labelcol)
    x_verification, y_verification = get_x_and_y(verificationData,labelcol)
    return ((x_training,y_training),(x_testing,y_testing),(x_verification,y_verification))

def runPipelineOnData(modelparams, x_training, y_training, x_testing, y_testing, x_verification=None, y_verification=None, epochs = 10, progressfile = "/common_shared/NN_progress", verification="/common_shared/NN_verification"):

    print(modelparams)

    tf.keras.layers.Dropout(.5)]
    with open(progressfile,"a") as f:
        f.write(str(modelparams))
    for param in modelparams:
        layers.extend([tf.keras.layers.Dense(param,activation="sigmoid"),tf.keras.layers.Dropout(.5)])
    layers.append(tf.keras.layers.Dense(1,activation="sigmoid"))
    model = tf.keras.models.Sequential(layers)
    model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=[tf.keras.metrics.AUC()])

    model.fit(x_training, y_training, epochs = epochs)
    with open(progressfile,"a") as f:
        f.write("Train AUC: "+str(model.evaluate(x_training,y_training)))
        test_auc = model.evaluate(x_testing,y_testing)
        f.write("  Test AUC:  "+str(test_auc)+"\n")
    if x_verification is not None:
        with open(verification,"a") as f:
            verification_auc = model.evaluate(x_verification,y_verification)
            f.write("Verification AUC:  "+str(verification_auc)+"\n")

#        pmml = KerasToPmml(model)
#        pmml.export(pmml_file)
    tf.keras.experimental.export_saved_model(model,"/common_shared/tensorflow_models/NN_"+"_".join([str(m) for m in modelparams])+"/"+str(time.time()))
    tf.keras.backend.clear_session()
    del model
    return test_auc
